    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ease the employment restrictions on asylum seekers.",
        "additional_details": "People seeking sanctuary in the UK could contribute \u00a342m/year; if the work restrictions were non-existent. Millions are being spent to support destitute asylum seekers each year; this capital is possible to retain & make better use of. \r\n\r\nhttps://www.gov.uk/guidance/immigration-rules/immigration-rules-appendix-k-shortage-occupation-list\r\n\r\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/oct/16/asylum-seekers-could-contribute-42m-to-uk-if-work-rules-relaxed\r\n\r\nhttps://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-45100120",
        "background": "Asylum seekers are restricted to jobs on the National Shortage Occupation List [SOL]; the reason behind their unemployed. The support they receive is inadequate for daily life [\u00a35.39/day]; forcing them to live in poverty; relaxing the terms will make lives less vulnerable for those already in agony.",
